data.text/markdown:
Dynasty Roto Roster Optimizer

This notebook optimizes a 26-player fantasy baseball roster using Mixed-Integer Linear Programming (MILP) to maximize wins against opponents across 10 scoring categories. Key Features:
  • All rostered players' stats count (not just starters)
  • Starting lineup slots enforce positional validity
  • Optimizes across 10 roto categories: R, HR, RBI, SB, OPS, W, SV, K, ERA, WHIP

Convert Fantrax Rosters

This step converts raw Fantrax roster exports to the pipeline format and applies automatic name corrections (accents, apostrophes, etc.). To update rosters:
  1. Download roster CSVs from Fantrax
  2. Place them in data/raw_rosters/ (my_team.csv + team_*.csv for opponents)
  3. Re-run this notebook
Load Data
Compute Opponent Totals
Filter Candidates
Solve Optimization
Results Summary
Team Comparison Radar
Win/Loss Matrix
Category Margins
Roster Changes
Category Contributions
Constraint Analysis

Sensitivity Analysis

Warning: This section takes 5-15 minutes to run as it solves a separate MILP for each candidate player. Run the cells below only when needed.
